    <string name="app_info">App Information</string>
    <string name="app_info_text">Mikamentos is a medication reminder app for elderly people.\n\nSTEP 1 - CREATE CATALOG:\nAdd your medications to the catalog with name and description. You can search descriptions automatically in medical databases (OpenFDA, CIMA, EMA). The ðŸ”„ button translates all descriptions into the selected language.\n\nSTEP 2 - SCHEDULE TIMES:\nFor each medication in the catalog, select the time and days of the week. You can set repetitions (1-10 times) with a custom interval between them.\n\nSTEP 3 - TAKE MEDICATIONS:\nAt the scheduled time, the alarm sounds and a voice announces: \"Time to take [medication]\". If there are several medications, they are announced one by one with a configurable silence interval (1-5 seconds). The screen stays on until the user dismisses the alarm.\n\nFeatures:\nâ€¢ Voice dictation â€” tap the mic to enter names and descriptions by speaking\nâ€¢ Listen button â€” tap the speaker icon to hear any description read aloud\nâ€¢ Alarm works with the app closed (foreground service)\nâ€¢ Voice customized with user title and name\nâ€¢ Configurable repetitions per medication\nâ€¢ 6 languages: Spanish, English, Slovak, Catalan, French, Italian\nâ€¢ Search medical descriptions online\nâ€¢ Automatic translation of descriptions\nâ€¢ 24h/12h time format\nâ€¢ User profile with voice recognition\nâ€¢ Share the app with friends via WhatsApp, Quick Share, etc.</string>
